} for, as it is always the same type as Silvally itself.\n* In [[Pokémon Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon]], Silvally is programmed to be able to be taught all three {{DL|Move variation|Pledge moves}} ({{m|Grass Pledge}}, {{m|Fire Pledge}}, and {{m|Water Pledge}}). However, due to a coding error, the [[Move Tutor]] will only ever offer to teach it Grass Pledge, making the latter two unable to be learned legitimately.\n\n===Origin===\nSilvally, like its pre-evolution {{p|Type: Null}}, seems to be based on a {{wp|chimera}}. Parts of it also resemble a {{wp|griffin}}. Silvally\'s concept also bears resemblance to {{p|Arceus}}. Like its pre-evolution, it also appears to be based on {{wp|Frankenstein\'s monster}} due to the bolt-like objects on its face and it being created from cells of different Pokémon types.\n\n====Name origin====\n<!--Do NOT add anything about Silicon Valley being a possible origin-->\nSilvally may be a combination of \'\'silver\'\' and \'\'ally\'\'. In-universe, it was named by Gladion.\n\nSilvady may be a combination of \'\'silver\'\' and \'\'buddy\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Normal|type2=Normal\n|ja=シルヴァディ \'\'Silvady\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'silver\'\' and \'\'buddy\'\'\n|fr=Silvallié|frmeaning=From \'\'silver\'\' and {{tt|\'\'allié\'\'|ally}}\n|es=Silvally|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Amigento|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'amigo\'\'|Spanish for friend}} and {{tt|\'\'argentum\'\'|silver}}\n|it=Silvally|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=실버디 \'\'Silbeodi\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=銀伴戰獸 / 银伴战兽 \'\'Yínbànzhànshòu\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|銀 \'\'yín\'\'|silver}}, {{tt|伴 \'\'bàn\'\'|partner}}, {{tt|戰鬥 \'\'zhàndòu\'\'|fight}}, and {{tt|獸 \'\'shòu\'\'|beast}}\n|zh_yue=銀伴戰獸 \'\'Ngàhnbuhnjinsau\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|銀 \'\'ngàhn\'\'|silver}}, {{tt|伴 \'\'buhn\'\'|partner}}, {{tt|戰鬥 \'\'jindau\'\'|fight}}, and {{tt|獸 \'\'sau\'\'|beast}}\n|ru=Силвалли \'\'Silvalli\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English 